00:40:42,109 --> 00:40:51,109
with two shlokas from Krishna to Uddhava,
from Uddhava to the Braja-gopis. And what

326
00:40:51,109 --> 00:41:00,160
does Guru Maharaj say in one shloka, his own?
yadamiya-mahimā-śrī-bhāgavatyāḥ kathāyāṁ

327
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:08,499
pratipadam anubhūtaṁ chāpy alabdhābhidheyā
tad akhila-rasa-mūrti-śyāma-līlāvalambaṁ

328
00:41:08,499 --> 00:41:19,349
madhura-rasa-dhi-rādhā-pādapadmaṁ prapadye
(Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī

329
00:41:19,349 --> 00:41:25,729
Mahārāj)
Although Her name is not mentioned, at every

330
00:41:25,729 --> 00:41:32,380
step, every shloka, every indication along
the way is to take one in the direction of

331
00:41:32,380 --> 00:41:39,059
the holy lotus feet of Srimati Radharani.
That’s Guru Maharaj’s shloka saying. And

332
00:41:39,059 --> 00:41:44,880
these eighteen thousand shlokas—what are
you supposed to understand from that—Radha-dasyam,

333
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:50,890
that the only thing in life, worth aspiring
for, is service to the lotus feet of Radharani.

334
00:41:50,890 --> 00:42:00,259
She controls Krishna. She has the copyright,
trademark, registered owner of Krishna. Go

335
00:42:00,259 --> 00:42:05,770
to Her and then you’ll get Krishna automatically.
Don’t waste your time trying to go directly

336
00:42:05,770 --> 00:42:14,229
to Krishna, He’s crooked.
… [śyа̄mam]̇tri-bhaṅga-lalitaṁ niyata-prakа̄śaṁ

337
00:42:14,229 --> 00:42:15,320
…
(Śrī Brahma-saṁhitā, 5.31)

338
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:21,480
That’s some indication of his ways.
aher iva gatiḥ premṇaḥ svabhа̄va-kuṭilа̄

339
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:24,599
bhavet …
(Śrī Caitanya-caritāmṛta, Madhya-līlā,

340
00:42:24,599 --> 00:42:30,269
8.111 and 14.163)
Autocrat, despot and liar—Krishna. Like

341
00:42:30,269 --> 00:42:37,690
the master chef: you’ve got your little…
your ingredients—gives that to the master

342
00:42:37,690 --> 00:42:44,589
chef and they’ll turn it into some inconceivably
nectarine substance. That’s our system:

343
00:42:44,589 --> 00:42:50,809
whatever, however, on whatever level this
resonates in your heart, you have some serving

344
00:42:50,809 --> 00:42:57,960
energy, some serving capacity—give that,
that little energy, whatever it is—give

345
00:42:57,960 --> 00:43:07,729
that, offer it to the lotus feet of Sri Guru.
So Uddhava aspires for it. Then this big buildup,

346
00:43:07,729 --> 00:43:14,610
what is it?—He’s saying, “Mahaprabhu
came down here to distribute something, but

347
00:43:14,610 --> 00:43:21,109
Swarup Damodar only really knows fully what
it is, Sanatan Goswami is worshiping it, Rupa

348
00:43:21,109 --> 00:43:27,809
Goswami is distributing it, Raghunath Das—and
Krishna Das by extension—they’re tasting

349
00:43:27,809 --> 00:43:38,269
it and instead of it becoming less tasteful
by their tasting it, it’s becoming increasingly

350
00:43:38,269 --> 00:43:42,210
tasteful.”
… śuka-mukhа̄d amṛtа-drava-saṁyutam

351
00:43:42,210 --> 00:43:44,839
…
(Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam, 1.1.3)

352
00:43:44,839 --> 00:43:54,780
It’s becoming even more pleasing. So, what
is it? And he says,

353
00:43:54,780 --> 00:43:58,269
… śrī-rādhā-pada-sevanāmṛtam aho
tad dātum īśo bhavān

354
00:43:58,269 --> 00:44:03,039
(Śrīmad Bhakti Vinoda-viraha Daśakam, 9)
Bhakti Vinod Thakur’s gift to the world

355
00:44:03,039 --> 00:44:07,979
is this prospect, this possibility: he’s
bringing us, giving us the opportunity to

356
00:44:07,979 --> 00:44:13,769
come in connection with the service of the
holy lotus feet of Srimati Radharani and that’s

357
00:44:13,769 --> 00:44:19,359
why Mahaprabhu descended.
yadi gaura nā hoita, tabe ki hoita,

358
00:44:19,359 --> 00:44:23,650
kemone dharitām de
rādhāra mahimā, prema-rasa-sīmā

359
00:44:23,650 --> 00:44:27,559
jagate jānāta ke
(Śrīla Vāsudev Ghoṣ)

360
00:44:27,559 --> 00:44:33,670
The great associates of Mahaprabhu—they’re
saying the same thing. Just it’s so beautiful

361
00:44:33,670 --> 00:44:44,000
that they can say it in a fresh and new, and
palpable, tasteful, meaningful way. That’s

362
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:45,869
why:
… śuka-mukhа̄d amṛtа-drava-saṁyutam

363
00:44:45,869 --> 00:44:47,119
…
(Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam, 1.1.3)

364
00:44:47,119 --> 00:44:52,960
It is becoming more relishable. When Guru
Maharaj expresses these things it becomes

365
00:44:52,960 --> 00:45:00,299
more relishable and it’s relishable by us,
he’s extending the capacity to relish this

366
00:45:00,299 --> 00:45:04,779
substance. That’s what is the
… tad dātum īśo … aho!

367
00:45:04,779 --> 00:45:08,779
(Śrīmad Bhakti Vinoda-viraha Daśakam, 9)
It’s the Sanskrit like for ‘ooh!’—that’s

368
00:45:08,779 --> 00:45:17,950
how you express astonishment and it’s in
Sanskrit ‘aho!’— “Ooh, Bhakti Vinod,

369
00:45:17,950 --> 00:45:24,239
this is your gift to the world, this is what
has come to us in the form of the Krishna

370
00:45:24,239 --> 00:45:31,759
consciousness movement. This is unthinkable,
unthinkable of unthinkable things. The, you

371
00:45:31,759 --> 00:45:38,499
know, impossible of impossible things. This
is your gift to the world.” That’s why

372
00:45:38,499 --> 00:45:44,450
Saraswati Thakur said, “Who wrote this?
Who wrote this?” They go, “Sridhar Maharaj.”—

373
00:45:44,450 --> 00:45:50,569
“No, Sridhar Maharaj has not written this,
Bhakti Vinod Thakur has written this through

374
00:45:50,569 --> 00:45:58,089
him.” It’s that perfect, the representation,
and very beautifully as Srila Keshava Maharaj

375
00:45:58,089 --> 00:46:04,589
said, reading Guru Maharaj’s writing—he
said, “The perfect combination of ontological

376
00:46:04,589 --> 00:46:13,809
substance and poetic beauty.” Someone can
put ontology there, but it’s not sweet.

377
00:46:13,809 --> 00:46:19,710
Someone can write some sweet rhyming words,
but there’s no substance, it’s sentiment.

378
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:29,489
Here we’re finding the highest philosophical
expression of the divine reality and sweetly

379
00:46:29,489 --> 00:46:37,710
expressed.
Brahma, Brahma-samhita—what did he said?

380
00:46:37,710 --> 00:46:38,710
… kandarpa-koṭi-kamanīya-viśeṣa-śobhaṁ
…

381
00:46:38,710 --> 00:46:46,150
(Śrī Brahma-saṁhitā, 5.30)
How beautiful is Krishna? Shobhana Krishna,

382
00:46:46,150 --> 00:46:54,799
Krishna-shobha. 10 million cupids personified
as one—that type of, it scares us, that

383
00:46:54,799 --> 00:47:01,299
thing. We think, “One cupid is more than
we can handle”—for this world, pivoting

384
00:47:01,299 --> 00:47:10,160
on the erotic principle. Here—10 million
cupids combined into one! Like the ladies

385
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:22,039
in Mathura when they see Krishna: lāvaṇya-sāram—
gopyas tapaḥ [kim acaran yad amuṣya rūpaṁ]

386
00:47:22,039 --> 00:47:27,130
lāvaṇya-sāram asamordhvam ananya-siddham
dṛgbhiḥ pibanty anusavābhinavaṁ durāpam

387
00:47:27,130 --> 00:47:31,499
ekānta-dhāma yaśasaḥ śriya aiśvarasya
(Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam, 10.44.14)

388
00:47:31,499 --> 00:47:35,390
gopyas tapaḥ kim acaran yad amuṣya rūpaṁ
…

389
00:47:35,390 --> 00:47:40,520
The first thing they think, “Krishna’s
so beautiful!”—this is how devotees think.

390
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:46,780
They think, “What do the gopis do that they
get to see Him all the time?” They’ve

391
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:51,219
just seen Krishna for the first time, we can
say—immediately they’re saying, “What

392
00:47:51,219 --> 00:47:56,290
do the gopis do—they get to see Him all
the time? Did they do some special... is it

393
00:47:56,290 --> 00:48:03,969
a special mantra? Then give me that mantra.
Or it’s like… You have to fast a certain

394
00:48:03,969 --> 00:48:08,640
way or at a certain time, or stand on one
foot, you know… —Just tell me what it

395
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:14,949
is, I want to get that! I want…” Krishna
is inconceivably beautiful:

396
00:48:14,949 --> 00:48:17,799
… lāvaṇya-sāram asamordhvam ananya-siddham
…

397
00:48:17,799 --> 00:48:21,210
(Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam, 10.44.14)
Inconceivably beautiful, lāvaṇya-sāram

398
00:48:21,210 --> 00:48:28,209
means like “beauty cream”, the cream of
all beautiful substance. Saying, “So, please,

399
00:48:28,209 --> 00:48:35,369
tell me, what did they do? What did they do?”
No, it’s not some particular austerity,

400
00:48:35,369 --> 00:48:42,309
they do things like that superficially. What
is it? They gave their hearts to Krishna,

401
00:48:42,309 --> 00:48:48,839
themselves heart and soul. That’s why Guru
Maharaj said, “When I think of Radharani

402
00:48:48,839 --> 00:48:56,160
I lose meself. So, when I think of Her level
of self-giving and self-sacrifice, everything

403
00:48:56,160 --> 00:49:05,710
else becomes trash.” He can say that, we
can’t really say that. As Guru Maharaj also

404
00:49:05,710 --> 00:49:12,410
said, “Our problem is this world, you know—we
like it or we think we do, or we think we’re

405
00:49:12,410 --> 00:49:25,670
going to find some way to adjust it, fine-tune
it in our favor. And we’re incessantly seduced

406
00:49:25,670 --> 00:49:31,540
by this prospect: that material happiness
is just around the corner, you know. Coming

407
00:49:31,540 --> 00:49:38,890
soon and… and we have to deal with that.”
What can break that?

408
00:49:38,890 --> 00:49:42,480
jāta-śraddho mat-kathāsu
nirviṇṇaḥ sarva-karmasu

409
00:49:42,480 --> 00:49:47,999
veda duḥkhātmakān kāmān
parityāge ’py anīśvaraḥ

410
00:49:47,999 --> 00:49:53,549
(Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam, 11.20.27)
“Liking this”—you don’t have to understand

411
00:49:53,549 --> 00:50:03,480
it, fortunately. It’s beyond human comprehension.
So sometimes Guru Maharaj said, “We’re

412
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:07,029
mad men having a mad talk.” Mahaprabhu says
that:

413
00:50:07,029 --> 00:50:08,869
а̄mi—eka bа̄tula tumi—dvitīya bа̄tula
…

414
00:50:08,869 --> 00:50:10,700
(Śrī Caitanya-caritāmṛta, Madhya-līlā,
8.291)

415
00:50:10,700 --> 00:50:16,829
“I’m the crazy number one, you’re crazy
number two for listening to Me.” That’s

416
00:50:16,829 --> 00:50:22,420
what he’s saying but:
yā niśā sarva-bhūtānāṁ

417
00:50:22,420 --> 00:50:26,420
tasyāṁ jāgarti saṁyamī …
(Bhagavad-gītā, 2.69)

418
00:50:26,420 --> 00:50:34,119
Actually, like what is, people may think what
Einstein and Niels Bohr, what they’re talking—that’s

419
00:50:34,119 --> 00:50:39,520
crazy. These Einstein and his friends, Einstein
and friends, you know— they’re crazy if

420
00:50:39,520 --> 00:50:46,130
you hear them talk. Or—is it: they’re
not so crazy, they’re talking about something,

421
00:50:46,130 --> 00:50:54,349
that’s actually very meaningful, very refined,
very real, very much real, not a mad fantasy.

422
00:50:54,349 --> 00:51:00,969
That’s the secret to that talk, yet the
people in general may think that it’s madness

423
00:51:00,969 --> 00:51:06,180
or be unable to penetrate. So much so that
Kaviraj Goswami said, “Actually these things

424
00:51:06,180 --> 00:51:12,030
should not be revealed. So why am I doing
it?” Gurudev said to Guru Maharaj about

425
00:51:12,030 --> 00:51:19,210
the Brahma Gayatri explanation, “Maharaj,
why are you revealing this? Not to. Maybe,

426
00:51:19,210 --> 00:51:25,400
better not to.” And Guru Maharaj said, “If
I don’t—who will?” And also, as Kaviraj

427
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:32,040
Goswami says, “If you’re not qualified
to appreciate this, you’ll just think, it’s

428
00:51:32,040 --> 00:51:35,910
madness,” he said, “so even though it
shouldn’t be spoken, I couldn’t be happier

429
00:51:35,910 --> 00:51:40,579
than knowing that only qualified people will
be able to appreciate it.”

430
00:51:40,579 --> 00:51:48,859
That’s what Srila Saraswati Thakur recognized
in Srila Guru Maharaj: the quality for this

431
00:51:48,859 --> 00:51:58,009
sort of depth of appreciation. The same thing
when Mahaprabhu sees the shloka of Rupa Goswami,

432
00:51:58,009 --> 00:52:04,190
the parallel shloka. Mahaprabhu before Jagannath
at the Ratha-yatra is singing the equivalent

433
00:52:04,190 --> 00:52:10,619
of a mundane song. I mean, to put in a modern
context, imagine: we’re at Ratha-yatra and

434
00:52:10,619 --> 00:52:18,690
then someone starts singing some mundane song
everybody knows from the radio.—And seems

435
00:52:18,690 --> 00:52:30,140
to be very moved by the whole thing. That
would be a test of faith. Those devotees,

436
00:52:30,140 --> 00:52:37,310
because they’re so qualified, they don’t
think anything of it. They can’t explain

437
00:52:37,310 --> 00:52:47,819
it, but it doesn’t bother them, they’re
lost in their own divine madness, we can say.

438
00:52:47,819 --> 00:52:54,829
But Swarup Damodar knows, svarūpa viditaṁ.
And then Mahaprabhu finds the shloka written

439
00:52:54,829 --> 00:53:05,329
on a bamboo, you’ve seen the way they etch,
that’s how the books—they still have them,

440
00:53:05,329 --> 00:53:13,739
here you can find them, with a pen—what
do you call it— a stylus, etching into the

441
00:53:13,739 --> 00:53:22,119
bamboo skin. Mahaprabhu sees the shloka. And
it’s revealing, unlocking all the mystery

442
00:53:22,119 --> 00:53:29,400
of what He’s singing before Jagannath. And
he shows it to Swarup Damodar and say, “How

443
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:37,950
can Rupa know this?” And Swarup Damodar—because
they know, only the two of them know—Swarup

444
00:53:37,950 --> 00:53:44,079
Damodar says, “Oh, well, how can anybody
know anything about Krishna consciousness?

445
00:53:44,079 --> 00:53:51,119
You must have revealed it to them, it must
have Your divine backing.” And this is the

446
00:53:51,119 --> 00:53:56,849
point: the same way Rupa Goswami’s saying…
“Oh, well we’ll never have that…”—No,

447
00:53:56,849 --> 00:54:00,680
everyone connected in this line, particularly,
by the grace of Srila Guru Maharaj, [he] is

448
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:07,599
getting access to those things. But how? If
there’s any appreciation, the same answer

449
00:54:07,599 --> 00:54:14,480
is there, “You must have given it to them”.
And that’s why Guru Maharaj, as exalted

450
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:23,130
as he was, amazingly revered everyone newly
connected to Krishna consciousness.

451
00:54:23,130 --> 00:54:32,959
This was not a posing on his part, he would
say, “We shall revere the person newly connected.”

452
00:54:32,959 --> 00:54:41,799
We think, “But wait, you’re the epitome,
Krishna consciousness personified.” And

453
00:54:41,799 --> 00:54:52,420
what is he saying at 92, “I am a student
and I shall forever remain a student.” He

454
00:54:52,420 --> 00:54:59,230
is our leader and he’s saying, “I am a
student.” The professor, the perfect professor

455
00:54:59,230 --> 00:55:05,749
saying, “I’m a student and I shall ever
remain a student.” Quoting Saraswati Thakur

456
00:55:05,749 --> 00:55:12,119
in Madras when teacher withdraws from the
class one of the advanced students becomes

457
00:55:12,119 --> 00:55:17,900
the monitor. That was his example, he’s
a perfect teacher, Guru Maharaj is saying,

458
00:55:17,900 --> 00:55:22,880
“I didn’t like to hear that example, I
don’t think of him that way.” But he’s

459
00:55:22,880 --> 00:55:29,779
presenting himself that way. Guru Maharaj
he’s saying at 92, “I’m a student. I

460
00:55:29,779 --> 00:55:36,940
shall forever remain a student.” The finite
is going to meet the infinite. Vrindavan Das:

461
00:55:36,940 --> 00:55:45,970
“according to the capacity”—a bird flying
in infinite sky—how high can you go? Or

462
00:55:45,970 --> 00:55:51,609
diving into an infinite ocean. When Mahaprabhu
is going to explain Bhakti-rasamrita-sindhu

463
00:55:51,609 --> 00:55:59,410
to Rupa Goswami, He is saying, “Rupa, the
length and breadth of this divine ocean is

464
00:55:59,410 --> 00:56:06,309
unlimited but I will take one drop and explain
that to you. And that’s also unlimited:

465
00:56:06,309 --> 00:56:12,970
a drop of the infinite is also infinite.”
So Srila Guru Maharaj said, “We shall revere

466
00:56:12,970 --> 00:56:20,920
even a new person because now they have a
connection with this divine substance. And

467
00:56:20,920 --> 00:56:27,029
maybe, we’re stagnating or not going, making
so much progress, and the new person will

468
00:56:27,029 --> 00:56:33,220
surpass me.” He said, “And if I properly
revere them and their connection with this

469
00:56:33,220 --> 00:56:41,989
divine substance, I’ll be in a position
to receive grace from them in the future.”

470
00:56:41,989 --> 00:56:50,369
So, this sort of insight, we can only think
of Mahaprabhu’s saying, “What is the unbearable

471
00:56:50,369 --> 00:56:57,289
suffering in this world?” You think: separation
from the devotee. Interestingly, there he

472
00:56:57,289 --> 00:57:08,239
doesn’t say “Krishna”—says “the
devotee,” but because it’s to include:

473
00:57:08,239 --> 00:57:18,589
without the devotee there is no Krishna. That’s
the long and short of it. Only a mirage of

474
00:57:18,589 --> 00:57:26,709
Krishna, a superficial representation of Krishna.
Without the devotee we have no Krishna. And

475
00:57:26,709 --> 00:57:31,589
that’s Guru Maharaj’s one of his other
favorites and that of Saraswati Thakur—from

476
00:57:31,589 --> 00:57:37,569
the Vilapa-kusumanjali of Raghunath Das Goswami.
āśā-bharair-amṛta-sindhu-mayaiḥ kathāṛchit

477
00:57:37,569 --> 00:57:42,430
kālo mayāti gamitaḥ kila sāmprataṁ
hi

478
00:57:42,430 --> 00:57:46,480
tvaṁ cet kṛpamayi vidhāsyasi naiva kiṁ
me

479
00:57:46,480 --> 00:57:51,579
prāṇair vrajena ca varoru bakarināpi
(Śrīla Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī. Śrī

480
00:57:51,579 --> 00:57:57,829
Vilāpa-kusumāñjali, 102)
This exclusive devotion to Srimati Radharani

481
00:57:57,829 --> 00:58:11,319
and Her extended self-surrogate Sri Guru.
[He is] saying, “My life is an aspiration

482
00:58:11,319 --> 00:58:20,880
to serve Your holy lotus feet, without which
of what value is my life?” This is how the

483
00:58:20,880 --> 00:58:26,390
servitor gauges the meaningfulness of their
existence. “My life is an aspiration to

484
00:58:26,390 --> 00:58:36,549
serve You. If that’s not possible then what
would I do with life?” And you say, “Oh,

485
00:58:36,549 --> 00:58:45,599
well you can go to Vrindavan.” [He] says,
“But without you, Guru, Sri Guru, what good

486
00:58:45,599 --> 00:58:54,839
is Vrindavan to me? And to ratchet it up further:
“And Krishna Himself is of no use to me

487
00:58:54,839 --> 00:59:06,319
without you.” So really the connection all
of us have with Krishna consciousness is through

488
00:59:06,319 --> 00:59:12,430
the devotees of Krishna. And it’s all—as
Guru Maharaj explains in his Gayatri:

489
00:59:12,430 --> 00:59:14,670
… bhargo vai vṛṣabhānu-jātma-
vibhavaikārādhanā-śrīpuram …

490
00:59:14,670 --> 00:59:18,039
(Śrīla Bhakti Rakṣak Śrīdhar Dev-Goswāmī
Mahārāj)

491
00:59:18,039 --> 00:59:25,260
“The whole spiritual world is a construct
